Etymology[edit]

From sub + pūs (“pus”).

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /supˈpuː.roː/, [sʊpˈpuː.roː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /supˈpu.ro/, [supˈpuː.rɔ]

Verb[edit]

suppūrō (present infinitive suppūrāre, perfect active suppūrāvī, supine suppūrātum); first conjugation

  1. I to gather matter, fester, suppurate
  2. I bring to a head
